article.headline: Jacksonville 75, North Florida 61
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Lehmon Colbert had 12 points and Tyrone Curnell came off the bench to score 11 points and grab 11 rebounds as Jacksonville defeated city rival North Florida 75-61 on Saturday. Curnell hit 4-of-11 shots and converted 3-of-5 free throws in recording the first double-double of his career. Jesse Kimbrough and Corey Claitt also had 11 points each. After connecting on 56 percent of their shots in the first half, Jacksonville managed just 29 percent from the field in the final 20 minutes. Jacksonville (11-11, 7-5 Atlantic Sun Conference) broke open a tight game in the first half by scoring 10 consecutive points to build a 12-point lead with six minutes left in the half and led at intermission 41-36. The Dolphins held a 54-52 lead near the midway point of the second half when they went on a 16-3 surge over the next seven minutes. That opened up a 15-point lead at 70-55 with 2:41 left in the game and put the game out of reach. Chris Timberlake and Aaron Caruthers led North Florida (2-21, 0-12) with 18 points each.
